g.text: Esprit de Corps: If only Kim were here right now! You could ask him if he sees a case here. The sight of those bullet holes stirs something in you.
You: "Okay. What can you tell me about this Revolution?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Not much. I don't have a *fresh perspective* on it. Shall we go?"
Visual Calculus: They look pretty ancient...
You: (Point to the chips in the wall.) "Someone has been shot! We're cops, we should solve it."
Kim Kitsuragi: He nods. "We should focus on present crimes -- from the present century."
You: "Okay. What can you tell me about the Revolution?"
Esprit de Corps: The sight of bullet holes stirs something in you, making you forget the lieutenant's surname.
You: "Oh, you mean like from the Revolution?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "There?" He looks to the wall. "Those are *old*."
Esprit de Corps: The fading marks are too degraded to draw any forensic conclusions. Just chips in the sandstone.
Kim Kitsuragi: "These bullets were fired during the Revolution, over half a century ago. They do not warrant investigation."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, the one that happened half a century ago." He blinks. "Those bullets were fired during the Revolution and do not warrant an investigation by officers of civil law."
